result.execSummary:
The defendant Miguel A Cano was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Use Fraud to Obtain Operator's License, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.14(5)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine and costs to be paid at $150.00 per month commencing 04-01-2016 or serve 35 days jail consecutive as penalty for non payment.
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
STAYED for 6 months.  If Defendant does not have any new law violations, the jail sentence will be permanently stayed.
To be completed by 08-19-2016 and to be monitored through WCS.

records.addlTxt: Affidavit for Services Rendered filed by Atty Sonderhouse.
with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Miguel A Cano in court with attorney Ronald James Sonderhouse.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter Dawn Maldonado appears.    Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds 
defendant guilty.  The Defendant was sentenced as follows: 
JAIL: 60 DAYS (stayed for 6 months, if the defendant does not have any new law violations the jail will be permanently stayed).
FINE: $1513.00 to be paid at $150.00 per month commencing 4/1/16 or serve 35 days jail consecutive as penalty for non payment.  
DNA SURCHARGE: $200.00 (to be paid consecutive to fine).
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
COMMUNITY SERVICE: Perform 50 Hours to be completed by August 19, 2016 and to be monitored through WCS.
